Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Commission Regulation (EC) No 238/94 of 2 February 1994 laying down detailed rules for the application in the pigmeat sector of the arrangements provided for in the Interim Agreement between the Community and Bulgaria and Romania (1),  and in particular Article 4 (4) thereof,
Whereas the applications for import licences lodged for the first quarter of 1994 are for quantities less than or equal to the quantities available and can therefore be met in full;
Whereas the surplus to be added to the quantity available for the following period should be determined;
Whereas it is appropriate to draw the attention of operators to the fact that licences may only be used for products which comply with all veterinary rules currently in force in the Community,
